  <source>Charite University, Berlin, Germany</source>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Background: Malnutrition is frequently occurring in sick patients and is associated with a
      higher morbidity and mortality. Muscle dysfunction is a common finding in malnutrition which
      leads to a reduced functional status and quality of life.

      Specific aims: The purpose of the study is to evaluate the effect of a three month
      nutritional intervention with oral supplements on nutritional status, muscle function and
      quality of life.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
